scription":"Run normalization repeatedly on the same raw response fixture and assert the resulting label is identical across runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.0,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"On repeated live API calls for the same document and taxonomy, the returned label remains consistent unless the provider response itself changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior text requires repeated live AI API calls and consistency tied to real provider responses. A mock fixes outputs and would hide model/provider variability; this is exactly LLM/ML-dependent execution, so Integration is disqualified.","test_description":"Execute N repeated real provider calls for the same document/taxonomy, capture raw provider outputs and final labels, and assert label changes only occur when raw provider response content changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before dispatch (for example truncate/reject according to policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at boundary between token-budget logic and dispatch path (e.g., over-budget requests still sent). In-process wiring with fake client is enough; no real OS/network/model judgment is required.","test_description":"Invoke classifier with documents near/over budget using configured policy, with a fake client; assert truncate/reject behavior and assert dispatch occurs or is blocked accordingly before any outbound call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays with